  <body link=#bbeeff" vlink="#ffffff" alink="#FF0000" style="background-color: #000000; color: #aaddff">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <h1>Astronomical Julian Period Day Number to </br>
        Julian Century Time t</h1>
    <h2>These terms are calculated with the Universal Time Coordinate<br />
        or GMT of the current time.</h2>
  <h3>
  The Ruby method is:
    
    <pre>
      def  time_julian_centurey(jd = ajd_time)
        # Time in fractional century
		  # Julian Period Day Number J2000.0 subtracted
	     # The J2000.0 epoch is precisely Julian date 2451545.0 TT (Terrestrial Time), or January 1, 2000, noon TT.
        # bd(var) is BigDecimal(var.to_s)
		  bd((jd - 2451545.0) / 36525.0)	  
      end
    </pre>
	 <% if @solar %>
    <p>
	   <input style="font-weight: bold" value="&nbsp;&nbsp;<%= @solar.ajd_time.to_s %>"/>  = AJPDN  +  Time.now.utc
    </p>
    <p>      
      <input style="font-weight: bold" value="&nbsp;&nbsp;<%= (@solar.time_julian_centurey * 1.0).to_s %>"/> = t   is time in fractional centurys since J2000.0
    </p>
    <p>
    This is used for the time parameter passed into most of the calculation methods.
    <% end %>
	 </h3>
